Another year at Whitefield Academy.

You've just finished a blissful summer during which you forgot almost everything you learned over the previous year.   Of course, since you're a witch, most of what you learned were spells and cantrips instead of algebra or history, but with enough television, you can forget anything.  Now you're back, with a mind almost as blank as your spellbook and a growing sense of dread.  What if you're the only girl who didn't bother to keep up with her studies?  The look on Headmistress Hannigan's face when you botch a simple spell -- the look that was like a distant bad dream while you were lying on the couch munching popcorn -- now floats up in your memory, all too real.

As you huddle in the back of the outboard motorboat, waiting for Stinglash Island to appear, you can't help but dwell on everything that could go wrong.    To make matters worse, you're arriving a day late.  You overslept yesterday and missed your ride to the island--which means you also missed the opening ceremony, the meet and greet, those lovely little pink cupcakes Mrs. Grislewood bakes...

Bleh.

"Here ya go, girl."  The old fisherman startles you out of your funk.   "Out ya get.  I don't have all day."

He bundles you out of the boat and onto the dock before revving the motor again and speeding off.  You watch him go, then turn to face the island.   The ivy-covered edifice of Whitefield stands solidly beyond the small forest, dominating the island.

You frown.  Someone could have come out to meet you, at least.  Maybe bring you a cupcake.

Where IS everybody?

Dock
You are standing on a dock on the western side of the island.  Rough waves lap at the wooden supports and crash against the narrow, rocky beach. Far to the southwest, you can just make out the lights of the town, shining through the morning mist;  to the east, a stone-lined path leads into the interior.
You can go east.
