> s

> s
As you walk towards the portal, the scent of fresh gingerbread becomes overwhelming.   You feel your appetite increased a thousandfold, and can't help stopping for a nibble.  A nibble turns into a chunk.  A chunk turns into a slab.   Before long, you're stuffing gingerbread into your mouth as fast as you can.  Oddly, you don't seem to be getting any fuller, and the idea delights you.  You could just stand here and eat this stuff forever!   You're dimly aware that you're going to get fat quick if you keep on like this, but it doesn't matter.  Nothing matters but the thought of more and more and more...

"WHO'S NIBBLING AT MY DOOR?" a furious voice bellows.  Startled, you take an involuntary step back.  That foot or two of distance weakens the door's scent just enough that reality intrudes, and you toss down a chunk of fattening masonry in horror as you backpedal towards the center of the rotunda.  You take a few deep breaths, trying to clear your lungs of the seductive aroma.

You hear muttering from near the door, but nobody emerges, and the sound quickly dies away.

You give yourself the old once-over.    You could swear your clothes feel tighter, but at least you haven't sprouted a tail or donkey ears or anything like that.  Still, probably better to avoid that door for now.
