PFEIFFER'S PICKLES

ANGLICIZED GARDEN FAERIES (FAERUS COTTINGLEYII) - This highly thaumogenic pest makes an excellent test subject.  Endemic in Britain, where a swarm can strip the average garden down to the dirt in under a minute, they are believed to have arisen in the region now known as the Sahara Desert.   While they are strictly herbivorous, it is advised that if you encounter a swarm in the wild, you do not move, as most species of garden fairy are attracted to motion -- a relic, it is believed, of the ancestral habitat, where they sought out trees blowing in the savannah wind.   Please make sure to close all windows/doors/etc. before extracting specimens!   This invasive species is devastating Europe, and the last thing we need is for them to escape into the North American ecosystem.

