The advisory reads as follows:

"ATTENTION ALL PERSONNEL!   Last year, we had a serious problem when some of the students got their hands on the Yeggle spell and broke into several locked areas.   Let's ensure that it doesn't happen again.  Please secure all important belonging magically and keep on the lookout for illicit Yeggle use."

You grin.   The Yeggle spell-- that's just what you need!   Luckily you used it so much last year you practically have it memorized.  You open your spellbook and...

...wait, how did it go again?

Were you supposed to close your eyes?   What did you do with your left hand?

Wonderful. You forgot Yeggle over the summer too.  Perfect.   If you could go back in time, you'd slap yourself.
