She looks at you disdainfully.  "Serioudly?  How'd you manadge to forgedd somethig like that?"    The girl on the card sighs, then holds up her wand.  "Here's how you do it.  Wadge."

You can't help but feel dumb as soon as she's showed you the movements.  Of course!  It was "right wrist bent up, twirl wand left twice", not "right wrist bent down, twirl wand right one-and-a-half times."   Oh well -- at least you've got it now.  You open your spellbook and jot down the full details of the Yeggle spell.

