> read hannigan file

> read hannigan file
This file concerns Henrietta Hannigan, the headmistress' granddaughter.   The only thing you know about her is what the headmistress told you, which is that she's well-nigh perfect and despite being much younger than the current Whitefield students could wipe the floor with all of them in any contest from magic duel to math test, not to mention looking like a perfect lady while doing it.

The reality, according to her report cards from Ravensdale Junior Academy, is that she's struggling to keep her head above water.  She got above-average grades in elementary school, but they've fallen off drastically, despite assurances from her teachers that she's putting in more effort that most of her classmates.   She has a very difficult time grasping abstract ideas and can barely do spells at all.   Her parents both hold doctorates (her mother in Atlantology, her father in physics) and while they love her dearly, they aren't doing a very good job of hiding their disappointment.   Henrietta is an obliging girl with a strong desire to please, and the situation is crushing to her.   She's been skipping meals and is showing signs of chronic depression, which is only worsening things.  She's poised on the brink of a spiral.

The second-to-last sheet of paper in the file is a psychiatrist's formal recommendation that Henrietta be placed in a remedial school for struggling witches.  Continuing in regular school, the analysis reads, could be a disaster, but if placed in a proper program, it might be possible for her to eventually reach the level of her peers.  The final sheet is a form officially welcoming her to Whitefield Academy.
