Someone's spread out a tarpaulin on top of some orange crates to make a bed, though not a very comfortable one.  The bed is sticky with sap and greenish stains.

Turning back the tarp, you find a deeply rent school uniform in a pool of foul-smelling sap.
> x uniform

> x uniform
It's a shredded school uniform, drenched in sap and rent in several places.   You can't tell for sure whose it is without picking it up.
> take it

> take it
Heart pounding, you turn the uniform over and read the name written on the collar.  J. Yoshida.

A blast of moist, fetid air hits the back of your head and you turn to find a towering plant creature standing behind you.  Snarling, it rips the clothes from your grasp and swings at you with one massive fist bristling with thorns.  You step back just in time.   Roaring and snorting, the creature forces you back, jealously guarding the bed and alchemy set.   You cautiously step back.  The horror shows little inclination to follow, but lets out a guttural sound which rises in intensity whenever you step toward it.
> x horror

> x horror
An enormous creature composed of a mass of plant matter.  Moss and bromeliads cover its broad back like a cloak, its lumbering green form is covered in thick, fibrous plates, tubers and vegetables mottle its skin like acne, and its tree-trunk sized fists bristle with thorns.  It is glaring at you in anger and confusion.
> aurale horror

> aurale horror
An extremely dark and powerful hex from the floralism school pervades the creature's body.
> open jar

> open jar
You twist off the lid.
The herbaceous horror, which has finally worked up the nerve to charge, draws to a halt as you point the mouth of the jar toward it and the faeries burst forth in a  voracious green cloud, cutting into the lumbering creature like a chainsaw.  It lets out a high-pitched keen of agony as they burrow into its flesh, and watery sap drains from its wounds.  The monstrosity dwindles to the size of a gorilla, then to a large man, and finally to the size of a girl.

In fact, as the faeries finish their savage banquet and peel off from the prone form, you see that it IS a girl.  It's Jenny Yoshida, one of your classmates.
She moans and stirs.  You help her over to her makeshift bed, where she pulls on what's left of her uniform.  Once she's had a moment to get her bearings, the two of you compare notes.

"It's fuzzy now," she says, "and all that time I was... that THING... feels like a dream, but I remember we were having a little party and--and I think we got attacked?   All these different spells...   Gwen just sort of froze--I think that happened first--and the Headmistress started, started shrinking I think--or maybe that was Tally--the Grizz was shouting something in, I don't know, German?"  She shakes her head.  "I'm sorry, I can't remember exactly, just that...whatever happened...it wasn't safe for us to stay there, so MJ and I made a break for the dorms.   We were going to-to just hole up on the east side and wait it out.  I thought I hadn't been enchanted, but then I started feeling strange.   I thought if I could make it to my alchemy set I could do something, but..."  She looks up suddenly.  "You haven't seen MJ, have you?"

You explain that you haven't, and she bites her lip, but she brightens when you tell her about Gwen.  "That's actually a good sign, if you think about it!  I mean, the spells that got me and Gwen, neither of them were fatal, right.  They just, just got us out of the way for a while, you know?  So, I'm sure the others are okay, just...stuck... somewhere."

She succumbs to a prolonged coughing fit.

"Ugh.  I feel terrible.  I think I'm going to hole up in here for a while until this stuff is out of my system.  I wish I was better at practical magic.  I'm pretty good at potions, though!  Maybe I can figure out one that will help Gwen, or something to help you--I'll put my recipe book out, so feel free to leaf through it!  I've got some things in my room that might be useful, too." She fishes a sheet of notebook paper out of her pocket and hands it to you.  "Here.  The password for the barricade.  It's, uh... well, just follow the instructions!"

She winks.  "I also bake a swell apple pie!"

