> read letter

> read letter
Dear Miss McBride,

Thank you for your letter in regards to my books.   You may be interested to know that I am working on another one, which should be released next year and expounds on my moral philosophy in a number of details only mentioned in passing in my earlier works.   I expect a young woman of your intellect and ability will find much in common with the story's heroine.

I have heard from many teen-aged readers who, like you, find themselves surrounded by mediocrity.   Unfortunately, the world is full of dull, cloddish people.  They greatly outnumber us.  Remember, your greatest asset is that you are human, with a human mind and human drives, and you can rise above the parasites.

Sincerely, A. R.
