The East Hall
This is the east side of the hall which runs around the central courtyard.  The floor is uneven and treacherous; it's covered with chunks of plaster from the ceiling, and thick roots have burst through the linoleum.  Further north, the hallway has collapsed in on itself and is filled floor-to-celing with rubble, rendering it impassable.   A few tough-looking vines twist through the wreckage.   Cracks have developed in the large plate-glass window here, making it hard to see, but you can still make out the gnome holes in the courtyard to the west.  Double doors to the east lead into the sparring dojo.
