Locker Room
An old, cement-floored locker room.   Most of the lockers have rusted shut.    The far wall is dominated by an industrial washing machine the size of a glacier, used for laundering the many intensely sweaty towels that a group of teenagers generates.  The exit to the north leads to the dojo, and the doors in the southeast corner lead out to the sports field behind the school.
You can go north or southeast.
You can see a washing machine.
> x washing machine

> x washing machine
The gigantic Bleach-O-Matic 5000 industrial washing system takes up a good percentage of the floor space.  Pipes lead into the sides, to carry scalding hot water, and the top is an octopus of vents and ducts to suck air down and blow steam out.  An automatic bleach dispenser is bolted to it.   The machine's sole control is a big rusty lever jutting from the side.   You can open and close the manhole-sized aperture on the front.
