Stables
The cavernous room smells like a cross between a reptile house and a bucket of rotten eggs.   The stables were a major selling point on the tour--what young witch wouldn't want to ride on her very own dragon?  Once you actually got into them, you learned why they were only showing you the outside.   Besides the smell, there's the fact that most of the barn-sized stalls sit empty; the school only owns one dragon, a broken-down nag who hasn't been awake since before the war.
You can go north.
You can see Princess and a supply cabinet.
