> use sock on window

> use sock on window
BA-BOOOOOM!

Shattered glass rains down around you in the aftermath of the explosion.    A gaping hole has been blown clear through, allowing you to step out into the courtyard.

You can't find the sock anymore.  At least it went out with a bang.
> w

> w
You pick your way over the shards of glass and step into the courtyard, blinking against the sunlight.  Ahead you spy a grassy field perforated by a series of gnome holes.   Wild gnomes can be spotted peeking fearfully out of some of them.    A towering mound of earth, produced by the gnomes' excavations, lies dead ahead.

As you get close to the mound, you hear a popping noise next to you feet.   "Back!  Back, you brute!" squeaks a tiny voice.   You look down and see a girl no more than three inches high brandishing a miniature gun at your shins.   You squint.   Is that... Tallulah McBride?

"Good God," she sneers.  "This is the biggest and ugliest one yet.  Back, I say!"  She punctuates her words with another burst of gunfire, then looks up at the sky, shaking her fist.  "I don't care how many of these blighted behemoths you send after me, you hear?  I'll blow them all to kingdom come!"
Before you can react, you hear a series of loud hoots echoing off the glassed-in walls.   An enormous silverback gnome, nearly a foot and a half tall, lopes across the dusty ground.   He darts forward, snatches Tally, and beats a hasty retreat in the direction of the mound, leaving a torrent of appalling, high-pitched curses in his wake.

"LeBlanc?" she calls abruptly.  "Is that you?   Bloody hell, you're gigantic!  Stop lolling about over there and lend us a hand!"

The gnome easily brachiates up the mound of earth and perches on top, examining his prize.

Courtyard
This is the school's central courtyard.  It's dry, dusty, and riddled with gnome holes.   There's a large dirt mound in the center.
You can go east.
You can see Tally McBride, a silverback gnome and a troupe of gnomes.
> x Tally

> x Tally
The gnome is pulling curiously on one of her arms.  "Ow!   You down there, stop gawping at me and do something about this beast!"
> x silverback

> x silverback
A burly specimen of gnomo habilis, a tool-using savannah species.    The silver-headed shovel strapped to his back, in place of the more typical flint or iron variety, marks him as a dominant male who's probably considerably tougher than the others in his band.

He is dangling Tally by the hair and poking at her curiously.
> x gnomes

> x gnomes
The gnomes mill about, wary of you, many of them only half out of their burrows and the others making sure there's a clear path of escape.   The lower-ranked males are much smaller than the silverback and sport loincloths and ragged goatees, while the females wrap their plump bodies in rabbithide and wear their hair in loose, messy braids.  Each adult carries a rough stone or iron shovel strapped to their back.    The children, which outnumber the adults, peer from behind their elders' backs with wide eyes.
> x mound

> x mound
A mound of loose dirt around fifteen feet tall.
> drop garden gnome

> drop garden gnome
You set the gnome down.
As soon as his feet meet the ground, his eyes lock with those of the silverback.   Sensing a rival male, the alpha gnome bellows and charges, tumbling down the mound in a landslide of dust and debris and launching himself at his challenger.   The garden gnome, uncomprehending, barely reacts, but it doesn't matter -- even solid muscle is no match for stone, and the silverback hits with a meaty thud and staggers back, battered and confused.   He attacks again, but this time his opponent understands the threat, and cracks the silverback's nose with one solid piston punch.  The silverback rallies again, and is pummeled in the chest, once, twice, three times, then clobbered with a powerful headbutt.

The silverback has had enough.  Bruised and chastened, he cedes to the new alpha male, retreating to the nearest hole to lick his wounds and slamming the door.   It opens again just long enough for him to angrily throw the silver-headed shovel -- symbol of his dominance -- directly at his successor.   The crude tool misses widely, bounces twice, and comes to rest in the dust.

The other members of the troupe emerge from their holes to examine the newcomer, patting his stony skin with their soft hands.    Several of them bring wheelbarrows filled with primitive pottery and fertility idols.

Tally slides down the mound, quite a distance for her, and stands up to dust herself off.  With feline dignity, she's obviously trying to pretend she wasn't just manhandled by a gnome and saved by the likes of you, as well as that she's not still three inches tall.   "Terrible blighter, that," she says airily.  "Thanks for the assist, but I'll be fine from here."

> take Tally

> take Tally
You pick Tally up and slip her into one of the side pockets of your knapsack.
