Library
Teetering shelves of books stretch to the ceiling, buttressed by bins of scrolls and grayish-yellow dunes of newsprint.   It would be impossible to find anything here on your own, but fortunately, an automat with the latest in positronic brains has been provided to help you check out.
You can go south.
> x automat

> x automat
This hulking yellow cabinet contains a number of glass doors, behind each of which you can see a book.   The automat was designed to keep track of student borrowing without the expense of hiring a librarian willing to report to the Headmistress about what the girls were reading.    You've been using it for two years, so you know the drill: the positronic brain's not that smart, but you can TALK to it, ASK  it about a book it's holding, or GIVE it a book in order to check it in.

The automat currently has the following books available to check out.
Mutiny on Pluto
Mother Nature's Spell: A Young Witch's Guide To The Magic of Growing Up
Poseidon's Treasures: A Salvager's Diary
