> read yarn

> read yarn
"August Fourth.   Sick with the rheum again; laid up for three days.   Think native boy is stealing my change.  Sure I had sixty cents in pocket yesterday--fifty today.  Counted twice.

August Fifth.   Much recovered.   Had words with native boy.  Had words with native boy's mother, who it turns out is also our cook.  Words escalate frightfully.   Hardtack for dinner.

August Sixth.   Approaching island of Papango; pearl divers swam out to meet us.   The girls of this island have a particular trick of turning into mermaids using a certain incantationa and series of motions -- see Fig. 2."

You stop reading, realizing what you've found.  The Mermaphro spell!  You jot it down in your notebook, looking forward to trying it out next time you're near the sea.

