> read embarrassing

> read embarrassing
As we become women, our bodies go through a period of changes called "puberty".  Some of these changes affect all girls.  Your non-magical friends are dealing with them, too.  But some of them are things that only young witches experience.   There is nothing wrong or shameful about these changes, but because non-magical people sometimes have difficulty in understanding them, you may find it easier to keep them private.

You may notice spells of headaches, dizziness, and strong, sudden emotions.  You may dream about strange or frightening things.   Sometimes witches dream of themselves hurting friends or loved ones.  It can be a very confusing and disturbing time.

What causes these effects?  Beginning at seven or eight years old, you body begins resonating with and producing traces of magic.  By twelve or thirteen, you have nearly the same magic power as you will as an adult.   Because you're not casting spells yet, this magic builds up with no way to release it.  Although it can be unpleasant, there's no reason to worry.  It's  all part of becoming a witch.

