> w

Plutovian Steam Cliffs
Towering cliffs, the face of which has been split by powerful geothermal activity.  Jets of steam spray forth, filling the air with scalding vapor.   A row of boulders and underbrush line the top of the plateau high above you.  It's possible to wend your way  west on the narrow trail and eventually make it to the top of the cliffs, but anyone up top would have a clear shot at you.   A  trail of trampled underbrush leads east into the jungle.
You can go east or west.
