> w
Lasers glitter through the air and nearly fry your toes off as you quickly leap back.  "Sorry, Comrade Blunderinski!" Jack Rocket hoots from somewhere behind the boulders atop the cliff.  "I'm not letting you anywhere near my ship until I get your un...con...DITIONAL surrender, do you hear?"
> wave flag

> wave flag
Jack pops up from behind the boulders, keeping his laser pistol trained on your heart.   "So... ready to pack it in, are we, you yellow-bellied Red?   I knew your oh-so-vaunted love for your comrades would crack out there in the Plutovian wilderness.  Come on up to the ship and we'll discuss the terms of your surrender."
> w

> w

The Atomic Yank
After climbing the cliffs, you reached a plateau, where you come face-to-face with the mighty Atomic Yank, pride of Earth.  This spaceship is sleek, silver, and cigar-shaped.  Unfortunately, it's a cigar that was half-smoked and then stubbed out on the rocky ground.  A landing ramp lolls crookedly out from the wreckage, and Jack Rocket stands across it, hands on his hips.

"Here's how this is going to go!  You're now the prisoner of Earth.  The first part of your punishment is for you to build a prison for me to keep you in.  You may come and go freely as needed to find rocks and other such necessities, but you may not enter the ship or talk to Stella.  I don't want your dirty philosophy anywhere near her pristine young mind!"   He frowns.  "I've faced worse villianesses than you before, and I know how to handle them.  I don't enjoy hitting women, but if you force my hand..."

"Page!"  Renee calls from the top of the ramp.  "Thank God you're still here!  Listen, you need to--"

"Get back in the ship, my young ward, you're not yourself!" Jack shouts.  He grimaces, and one of the green lights on his helmet goes red.  The ship's hatch slams shut in Renee's face with a solid click.  Jack turns back to you, grimly determined, and plants his feet firmly on the ramp.
You can go east or in.
You can see Jack Rocket.
