> x Jack
A handsome man in a tight, shiny space uniform.   He's standing with his hands on his hips, regarding you coldly.
> talk to Jack

> talk to Jack
"I don't break bread with Communists, sister!"
> kiss Jack

> kiss Jack
Jack raises his fists as you approach, but lowers them as you bring your face close to his.  "Natasha?   What are you doing?"

You lower your eyelids and lick your lips.   You're trying to be seductive, but it looks more like you're eating ice cream while sleepy.   It seems to be working on Jack, though... he's sweating profusely and getting flustered.

"No... you...you Trotskyite temptress!" he says, taking a step back.  "Stalinist slattern!  Lust-laden Lenin-loving louse!  We can't...not here... er, not anywhere, I mean... get those--those beautiful blue eyes away from me!  I won't be distracted by a pretty face!  Not again!  Not this -- EUUUUUUUGGGNNNHH!"

His defenses were so low that even you were able to manage beaning him, and pretty solidly too.  He collapses and slides down the ramp like a sack of potatoes.   The light on his helmet goes green.  You hear a click, and the door to the Atomic Yank slides open again.
> x Jack

> x Jack
A handsome man in a tight, shiny space uniform.  He's lying at the base of the gangplank, knocked cold.
> in

> in
You walk up the gangplank to the ship and step through the portal.   Renee is here, perched on one of the control panels with a miserable look on her face.

She brightens at once when you enter.  "Page!  You have no idea how glad I am to see you.  Until you showed up, I was starting to think I was trapped here forever.   And believe me, THAT guy out there is only good in small doses and from the other side of the page.  Not to mention he thought I was his irritating little sidekick, who also happens to be the one woman in the known universe he doesn't want to -- um, let's just say, I've had enough of Pluto.   Let's go."  Her face suddenly falls.  "We CAN go, right?  Please tell me you didn't just get trapped here too."

You explain about the portal, and she laughs in relief.  "Thank God.  In that case, let's get out of here before I get any more demerits.  I'll bet Hannigan is already blowing her top over me not showing up to that little reunion party she's got planned."

You tell Renee about the situation at school, and she listens with growing interest.  "Really, now!  Well, THAT certainly sounds suspicious.  And given that, I doubt it's a coincidence that what should have been a non-magical book instead got  me stuck in a fictional jungle on the far edge of the solar system."

She hops off the panel.  "Listen, I'm going to head down and look for that portal back before I cook like a ham in this suit.  I'll be in the room if you need me, okay?"  She squeezes your arm.  "And thanks.  Really.  I think if I'd heard one more monologue about the Uranian Fuel Wars I would have jumped off that cliff over there just to get away."

