> mermaphro me

> mermaphro me
You tap yourself with the wand and perform the motions--a rapid curlicue flick of the wrist, eight times.  Your legs feel soft and clammy.   They're turning into a mermaid's tail!   You plop down on the dock, feeling your bones warp and soften and your legs elongate and... and fuse?

They're not fusing.

In fact, they seem to be splitting!

By the time the spell is finished, it's become obvious that you're no delicate mermaid, but a tough, eight-tentacled octopusmaid.  You raised a hand to your neck.  You've still got those tubey breathy things that octopi have, so you should be able to go under water. That was the important part, anyway.  Your flop your hand back and forth in front of your face.  You don't seem to have bones anymore, which makes it hard to remain upright.

Feeling your lungs (or...whatever) begin to ache, you slither off the edge of the planks and plop into the sea, gratefully sucking in a whateverful of water.

Under the Dock
The underside of the dock is choked with seaweed and debris.    The coastline in both directions is tangled and overgrown, so your only real choices from here are to undo the Mermaphro spell and go back topside, or to swim west into the open sea.
You can go west.
"Sure, just hop right in," pipes up a little voice from your knapsack.  "It's not as if I still need air or anything.   I've got a nice air pocket back here, thanks so much for your concern."
