Sunlight Zone
You're gliding beneath the bright, sunlit surface of the sea.    If you were human, the water here would be freezing, even in early September, but in your current form it feels quite pleasant.   It's almost as if you're on a nice stroll in the country, except instead of walking you're gulping down water and expelling it to jet along in a process that you'd rather not think about too hard.   Stinglash Island lies to the east, while the coast of the Olympic Peninsula is far to the south--too far to swim without a good reason.    Beneath you stretches the darkness of the deep water.
You can go east or down.
