You hope the cryoglazed ice is tough enough to hold against the pressure on the way up.  If it breaks off, you're going to have a very heavy block of stone heading straight back towards you.

On the other hand...if it doesn't break, it's going to be moving pretty fast by the time it reaches the surface.  Who knows where it'll end up?
