You are standing on a dock on the western side of the island.  Rough waves lap at the wooden supports and crash against the narrow, rocky beach. Far to the southwest, you can just make out the lights of the town, shining through the morning mist;  to the east, a stone-lined path leads into the interior.
You can go east.
