Rotunda
You are in the central rotunda of the school, just under the turquoise dome.  A beautiful mural adorns the circular ceiling, but the rest of the room looks like a junk heap.  Tables are overturned, puddles of punch are splattered across the floor, and loose balloons bob listlessly around the upper reaches.

The foyer and the exit lie to the west.  To the north are the administrative offices, and to the south, where the dining hall used to be, is a curious round portal made of gingerbread.    A grand staircase leads up the second floor of the rotunda.
You can go west, north, south, east or up.
You can see a punchbowl, a welcome banner, Gwendolyn Marx and puddles.
