Delicate China Nook
This is the ruins of the display nook for Headmistress Hannigan's private collection of china, the pieces of which are scattered around the room in forms ranging from shards to powder.  There's a gaping hole in the ceiling and a large impact crater directly beneath it, in which is lodged a cracked sarcophagus crusted over with ice.
You can go north.
You can see a crater full of china dust and a broken sarcophagus.
