It's a trophy for Excellence in Institutional Mass Meal Preparation, presented to Baba Grislewood in 1951 by the Greater Pacific Rim Cafeteria Organization.   That's pretty impressive, even if it does appear to be a repurposed bowling trophy.    On top, there's a little statue of a man just about to throw a bowling ball.
