Secret Tunnel
You open the door, revealing a spiral staircase decending into pitch darkness, and carefully start down.  Despite the lack of any visible light source, you find yourself easily about to make out what's ahead thanks to the enchanted glasses. This must be the reason Gwen never stubbed her toe or tripped over anything whenever the two of your sneaked out after curfew... it would have been nice for her to let you in on the secret!

After descending about twenty feet, you find yourself facing a winding passage burrowing further ahead to the southeast, beneath the school.   A secret escape tunnel?  The entrance to a dungeon?  What it is, Hannigan's got to be at least a little less stodgy than you've always assumed.
