The wooden stairs creak underfoot as you chamber up.  You don't think much of it until you get to the top step and reach for the knob, at which point you hear a voice from the other side of the door.

"Is--is someone down there?"

You freeze, fingers inchs from the knob.  Suddenly, the door jerks open.  You're standing face-to-face with a girl in her early teens, with platinum-blonde hair and a look of dawning horror on her face.    She turns tail and runs before you can say anything.

"Grandma!  Grandma!  Help!"

