Living Room
A cozy living room.  A set of furniture, threadbare but spotless, is arranged around a well-polished radio set.   There's a kitchen to the north, and the house's front door lies to the east.
You can go north or east.
You can see Henrietta Hannigan and a radio.
The girl you saw earlier is here, blocking the front door with her wand raised.  She's clearly terrified, but she's not giving any ground.

"I'm n-not scared of you!" she says defiantly, throwing one arm across the door.  "And you're not getting near my grandma!"

You ask who she is.

"H-Henrietta," she gulps.  "I mean--I mean, it's none of your business!  And I know who you are.  You're one of the bad girls from the school Grandma warned me about.  She said you were all, all--"

She takes a deep breathe.

"--all a bunch of hoodlums and lowlives!"
And where is the headmistress, you ask?  Outside?

"M-maybe, but you aren't getting past me.   We're going on a trip.  Grandma's going to help me with my magic.  She said... she said she didn't have enough money to fix up the school and that she had to give space to a bunch of trollops and third-raters just to keep the lights on, and that wasn't fair and I would never catch up that way, so she set up some tricks so all the bad girls would be scared away."

And let me guess--she's got Dark Overload insurance that guarantees her a fat payout in the event of just such a tragic event, I'll bet?  Enough to fix up the school and hire a real staff?

"I...I don't know," Henrietta stammers.  "She said... she said we should pretend an evil witch did it.  But it's not hurting anyone!  It's helping!  She'll be able to offer good, rigorous schooling like in the olden days, none of this newfangled modern stuff!"

That's what you want, huh? you ask.  Extra-hard school?

"Grandma says that's what I need.  That's why I'm not good at magic, because modern schools have been too soft with me.   Everybody thinks I can't do it.  Even my own mom and dad think I'm stupid!"   Her eyes are shiny.  "Grandma's the only one who believes in me!"

She raises her wand.  "And I won't let you hurt her!"
