> cryoglaze headmistress
The water hardens into a solid shell.  You hold your breath, and then--

"Oh, good show, Miss LeBlanc, good show!  You actually managed to display the barest glimmer of scholarship!"   The Headmistress breaks out of the cryoglaze easily, scattering lumps of ice around the sand.  "Let's try something a little more complicated, shall we?"

She snaps her fingers, and a large shield materializes in her hand, a golden disc decorated by the face of a lion frozen in mid-snarl.

"Let's see how you handle an elementary shield spell, Miss LeBlanc."
> envive shield

> envive shield
The lion's head bursts to snarling life, its powerful jaws snapping inches away from the Headmistress' face.  She frowns and dismisses it in a puff of smoke.  "Have you actually been applying yourself in my absence, Miss LeBlanc?   I see I'll have to eschew form in favor of function.  Orbus!"   She waggles her fingers and eight steel balls of various sizes appear, orbiting her at breakneck speed.

"I don't supposed you paid attention in Cosmology, but these are the planets--quite a bit smaller than the real thing, but fast enough to pack a punch.  I wouldn't advise getting too close, or trying to grab them.... a hit with one of these could give you a broken bone for your trouble.
> mermaphro me

> mermaphro me
You transform yourself and flail forward in a burst of gooey hysteria, grabbing the metal balls with your tentacles and wrapping your boneless arms around the Headmistress.  She flings you off in disgust, stepping back against the Packard.  "Enough of this!"

Walking around the rear of the car, she taps herself with her wand, enveloping her form in a shield of red light.  "There.  No more half measures.  With this spell, no magic can touch me.  No ice, no fire, no lightning, no poison gas; no spell gets through this barrier."  She leans forward over the Packard's trunk, keeping the frame of the solidly built car in between you and her.  "And if you entertain any fantasies of thrashing me with your fist, as I'm sure a little thug like you does with some regularity, well -- I assure you, you'll never get close enough."
> yeggle Packard

> yeggle Packard
The trunk pops open, slamming the Headmistress right in the jaw and knocking her cold.   You take the opportunity to punch her several dozen more times before tying her up, gagging her, and taking her wand, and even so, you're not really sure things you're safe until Gwen and Mrs. Grislewood appear from the forest.   Jenny follows them, carrying a sleeping potion, which she dribbles into the Headmistress' slack mouth.

"Nice work, P," Gwen says, grinning.  "I knew you had it in you."

A few hours later, you're in Port Querubin, describing the day's events to the police.
"We've called your parents," the tired-looking police sergeant says, rubbing his temples.   "In the meantime, we'll find a place for you in town for the night--"

One of the other officers leads Henrietta past you.  She looks like she's been crying, but she smiles shyly when she sees you.   "I talked to my mom and dad about--well--everything.  I'm going to go to that school we talked about.   I think--I think things will be a little better."

You sit back in the hard plastic chair, exhausted.  It's been a long day, but you did it -- you saved all the students.  You saved yourself.   You even saved the lunch lady.   You don't know what's going to happen to the school now.  Is it going to be closed?  Sold?  Renovated?   Are you going to be stuck somewhere else?

Oh well.   You can worry about all that tomorrow.

THE END
